## 1. POST /create-account — Create a Salesforce Account

**What it does** (1–3 sentence narrative explaining the business purpose, downstream side effects, and any gotchas):

> Creates a new Salesforce Account from the supplied JSON body. The request fields use Salesforce PascalCase field names (e.g. `Name`, `BillingCity`) and are passed straight through to the Salesforce SOAP API after stripping nulls. Returns the new Salesforce Id on success.

### Request

- **Method**: `POST`
- **Path**: `/api/v1/create-account`
- **Auth**: none (local dev)
- **Headers**:
  | Header | Required | Example |
  |---|---|---|
  | `Content-Type` | yes | `application/json` |

- **Body** (`application/json`):
  | Field | Type | Required | Description | Example |
  |---|---|---|---|---|
  | `Name` | string | **yes** | Account name | `"Nebula Cloud Systems"` |
  | `Industry` | string | no | Industry vertical | `"Technology"` |
  | `BillingCity` | string | no | City | `"San Francisco"` |
  | ... | | | | |

### Demo Request (PowerShell)

```powershell
$body = @{
  Name = "Nebula Cloud Systems"
  Industry = "Technology"
  BillingCity = "San Francisco"
} | ConvertTo-Json

Invoke-RestMethod `
  -Uri "http://localhost:8081/api/v1/create-account" `
  -Method POST `
  -Body $body `
  -ContentType "application/json"
```

### Demo Request (curl)

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8081/api/v1/create-account \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{ "Name": "Nebula Cloud Systems", "Industry": "Technology", "BillingCity": "San Francisco" }'
```

### Success Response — `201 Created`

```json
{
  "id": "001XXXXXXXXXXXXAAA",
  "status": "created"
}
```

### Error Responses

| Status | Code | When | Example body |
|---|---|---|---|
| 400 | `BAD_REQUEST` | Required field missing or invalid | `{ "code": "BAD_REQUEST", "message": "Name is required" }` |
| 422 | `SALESFORCE_REJECTED` | Salesforce rejected the create (validation rule, dup, etc.) | `{ "code": "SALESFORCE_REJECTED", "message": "DUPLICATE_VALUE: ..." }` |
| 503 | `SALESFORCE_UNAVAILABLE` | Cannot reach Salesforce | `{ "code": "SALESFORCE_UNAVAILABLE", "message": "..." }` |
| 500 | `INTERNAL_ERROR` | Anything else | `{ "code": "INTERNAL_ERROR", "message": "..." }` |

---

## Conventions

- All success responses are `application/json`
- All error responses follow the standard error shape: `{ code: string, message: string }`
- Timestamps (when used): ISO-8601 UTC, e.g. `2026-04-29T12:00:00Z`
```

---

## Quality Bar — Each Endpoint Section MUST Include

- One-line summary in the index table
- "What it does" narrative — explains purpose, side effects, anything subtle a caller should know (NOT just a re-statement of the path)
- Method, path, auth, required headers
- Full body schema as a table (not just a reference to the RAML — duplicate it here for readability)
- **At least one realistic demo request** in BOTH PowerShell (`Invoke-RestMethod`) AND curl
- Success response example with realistic values
- Every error response with: status, code, when it fires, example body

If any of these are missing, the agent MUST fill them in before declaring the work done — never a `TBD` in `API.md`.

---

## Cross-File Consistency Rules

Whenever an endpoint changes, the agent MUST update ALL of these in the same response:

| File | What to update |
|---|---|
| `src/main/resources/api/<api>.raml` | Spec (types, examples, responses) |
| `src/main/mule/<feature>-api.xml` | Flow & error handling |
| `src/test/munit/<feature>-api-test-suite.xml` | New/updated test case |
| `API.md` | Endpoint section + index row |
| `PROJECT_CONTEXT.md` § 4 (API Inventory) | Status flags |

Treat `API.md` as a first-class deliverable. If it drifts from the actual flow, the project is broken.
